This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with Neural Machine Translation (NMT) and proposes a new technique for generating synthetic parallel data. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves training a model to improve translation quality. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of machine learning techniques for language translation. It may also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the use of neural networks for translation. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it involves the use of techniques for improving the quality of image captioning.
